The funny thing is, the line of questioning on Indexing is kind of subjective and I&#039;d probably have a field day with them on it.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
e.g.&lt;br /&gt;
Are clustered index scans beneficial to an execution plan?&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
and then ask&lt;br /&gt;
Are there any performance issues with having a lot of indexes on a table?&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
First, you can&#039;t answer the first question on if it is beneficial or not unless you have a description of a lot of variables to the equation.  The second is a common question but again, depends on how it is being asked.  &lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
